name: Face to Face
overview: Bjørn investigates the killing of his daughter. People around him believe she might have committed suicide, but he doesn't accept that. Both the stakes and the suspense rise relentlessly as Bjørn inches closer to the truth.

episodes.name: Forensics
episodes.overview: Investigator Bjorn is called to the morgue for an ordinary identification and is faced with a hard truth; the body belongs to his daughter. Although all clues point to a suicide, he fixates on a tiny clue that proves otherwise.

episodes.name: The Apartment
episodes.overview: Bjorn is led to a luxury apartment where he encounters an unknown young woman, who turns out to be his daughter’s wife. Soon, he starts piecing together the puzzle of his daughter’s life, and it is darker than he ever thought.

episodes.name: The Brothel
episodes.overview: Inspector Bjorn arrives at a luxury brothel to find the prostitute who introduced his daughter to prostitution. As he later finds out, they enjoyed together a sinful life crawling with parties, drugs, sex and fast money.

episodes.name: The Nightclub
episodes.overview: Bjorn meets with a notorious club owner, with whom he made shady deals in the past. He reveals shocking information about Bjorn’s daughter, and makes him face a harsh truth; his daughter was not the innocent girl he remembered.

episodes.name: The Police car
episodes.overview: The clues lead Bjorn to a corrupted cop he used to work with in the past. Although he tells him many lies, Bjorn knows that he met with his daughter the night she died, and he tries to cut through the lies to uncover a major clue.

episodes.name: The Traveler's Course
episodes.overview: The clues lead Bjorn to a corrupted cop he used to work with in the past. Although he tells him many lies, Bjorn knows that he met with his daughter the night she died, and he tries to cut through the lies to uncover a major clue.

episodes.name: The Morgue
episodes.overview: Finally convinced that his daughter committed suicide, Bjorn meets with his ex-wife to say their final goodbye to their child. But as they are mourning over the casket, Bjorn notices a small detail that could change everything...

episodes.name: The Last Stop
episodes.overview: Bjorn confronts the coroner, who tries to persuade him to seek for psychiatric help. But the detective has connected the dots, and is certain he now knows the truth. All he wants is revenge...

episodes.name: The Private Clinic
episodes.overview: Susanne mourns the loss of her daughter. When the doorbell rings, she is confronted by a man John, who wants help to stop smoking. During the hypnosis, John reveals something shocking.

episodes.name: The Police Academy
episodes.overview: Susanne seeks out Police Commissioner Richard to tell him about the mysterious man. Richard has no knowledge of the man or cases of murder of young women. But he asks Susanne for a favor.

episodes.name: The Normal House
episodes.overview: Susanne meets Officer Louise, who turns out to be a former client, whom she helped after a rape. When Susanne discovers that the police commissioner is calling Louise, she's sure something's wrong.

episodes.name: The Prison
episodes.overview: Under the pretext of having to make a psychological assessment, Susanne lies in to confront her ex-husband Bjørn, who is in prison after murdering Frank, who Bjørn thought was their daughter's killer.

episodes.name: The Strip Club
episodes.overview: Susanne finds Sapphire at the strip club and finds out she knows the suspected hitman John. But Sapphire is not only a witness - she is also a target.

episodes.name: The Tracker
episodes.overview: Susanne desperately needs help finding the girl and contacts CC, a former soldier she has had in therapy for PTSD. Reluctantly, he agrees to track down the girl.

episodes.name: The Train
episodes.overview: At the train station, Susanne sees her former colleague Maja and discovers that Maja has had a session with Sapphire and that she is connected to both the Police Commissioner and John.

episodes.name: The Secret Place
episodes.overview: John kidnaps Susanne and takes her and Sapphire to a deserted island in the harbor. Bound and in mortal danger, Susanne must use all her psychological abilities to survive.
